description.how: Traders exchange funds through request for quotation system built on 0x protocol.
description.who: LON tokenholders own and govern the protocol. They currently take all of the total trading fees paid by traders (protocol revenue). imToken's investors include IDG Capital, Qiming Venture Partners, Breyer Capital, etc.
description.what: Tokenlon is a non-custodial exchange protocol built on Ethereum. Tokenlon was founded by imToken team and launched in 2018.
description.funding: imToken has raised approx. $10M from IDG Capital, etc.
description.competition: Centralized exchanges such as Coinbase, Kraken and decentralized exchanges such as 0x, Bancor, Kyber.
description.business_model: Tokenlon is an AMM-based exchange (DEX) built on Ethereum (by the imToken team).

description.how: Liquidity providers deposit funds into Trader Joe and receive trading fees from traders (supply-side revenue).
description.who: JOE tokenholders own and govern the protocol. They currently take a cut of the total trading fees paid by traders (protocol revenue). Trader Joe's investors include Three Arrows Capital, DeFiance Capital, GBV Capital, Mechanism Capital, etc.
description.what: Trader Joe is a non-custodial exchange protocol built on Avalanche (originally a fork of SushiSwap). Trader Joe was founded by an anonymous team and launched in 2021.

description.how: Users deposit funds into UMA and mint synthetic assets. Counterparties can call the oracle to settle disputes. Oracle participants receive oracle call & periodic fees from users (supply-side revenue).
description.who: UMA tokenholders own and govern the protocol. They do not currently take a cut of the total oracle call & periodic fees paid by users (protocol revenue). UMA's investors include Placeholder, IOSG Ventures, etc.
description.what: UMA is a non-custodial derivatives exchange & oracle protocol built on Ethereum. UMA was founded by Allison Lu & Hart Lambur and launched in 2020.
description.funding: UMA has raised approx. $4M led by Placeholder VC.
description.competition: Decentralized derivatives platforms such as Synthetix, Augur, Flux Market.
description.business_model: UMA is a derivatives exchange (DEX) built on Ethereum.

description.how: Liquidity providers deposit funds into Uniswap and receive trading fees from traders (supply-side revenue).
description.who: UNI tokenholders own and govern the protocol. They do not currently take a cut of the total trading fees paid by traders (protocol revenue). Uniswap's investors include Paradigm, a16z, USV, etc.
description.what: Uniswap is a non-custodial exchange protocol built on Ethereum. Uniswap was founded by Hayden Adams and launched in 2018.
description.funding: Uniswap has raised approx. $12M from Paradigm, a16z, Union Square Ventures, etc.
description.competition: Centralized exchanges such as Coinbase, Kraken and decentralized exchanges such as 0x, Bancor, Kyber.
description.business_model: Uniswap is an AMM-based exchange (DEX) built on Ethereum.

description.how: Overcollateralized borrowers deposit funds into Unit Protocol and receive USDP.
description.who: DUCK tokenholders own and govern the protocol. They currently take a cut of the total interest paid & liquidations paid by borrowers (protocol revenue).
description.what: Unit protocol is a non-custodial lending protocol for stablecoins built on Ethereum. Unit Protocol was founded by Artem Zakharov and launched in 2019.

description.how: Lenders deposit funds into Venus and receive interest payments from borrowers (supply-side revenue).
description.who: XVS tokenholders own and govern the protocol. They currently take a cut of the total interest, liquidations, withdrawals & deposits paid by borrowers (protocol revenue).
description.what: Venus is non-custodial lending & stablecoin protocol built on Binance Smart Chain and other blockchains (originally a fork of Compound & MakerDAO. Venus was founded by Joselito Lizarondo and launched in 2020.
description.funding: NA.
description.competition: Centralized lending platforms such as BlockFi, Binance and decentralized lending platforms such as Aave Compound & platforms that offer stablecoins such as USDC, USDT, and DAI
description.business_model: Venus is a lending platform, which also offers access to a USD-pegged stablecoin called VAI. It's built on multiple chains (fork of Compound & MakerDAO).

description.how: Liquidity providers deposit funds into Vesper Finance and receive a return on investment (supply-side revenue).
description.who: VSP tokenholders own and govern the protocol. They currently take a cut of the total return on investment & withdrawal fees paid by liquidity providers (protocol revenue). Vesper Finance’s investors include A195 Capital, CMT Digital, Kenetic Capital, etc.
description.what: Vesper Finance is an asset management protocol built on Ethereum. Vesper Finance was founded by Bloq and launched in 2020.

description.how: Liquidity providers deposit collateral and mint volatility tokens. Traders can then purchase these volatility tokens to express views on market volatility.
description.who: The Volmex team and investors own and govern the protocol. They currently charge a minting and redemption fee (protocol revenue). Volmex’s investors include Three Arrows Capital, Robot Ventures, CMS Holdings etc.
description.what: Volmex enables VIX-like indices for crypto assets and trading functionality on Ethereum. Volmex was founded by Cole Kennelly and launched in 2021.

description.how: Liquidity providers deposit funds into WakaSwap and receive trading fees from traders (supply-side revenue).
description.who: WAKA tokenholders own and govern the protocol. They currently take a cut of the total trading fees paid by traders (protocol revenue).
description.what: WakaSwap is an automated market-making (AMM) decentralized exchange (DEX) for the Fantom Opera network. WakaSwap was launched in May 2021.

description.how: Liquidity providers deposit funds into yearn.finance and receive a return on investment (supply-side revenue).
description.who: YFI tokenholders own and govern the protocol. They currently take a cut of the total return on investment & total assets under management paid by liquidity providers (protocol revenue).
description.what: yearn.finance is an asset management protocol built on Ethereum. yearn.finance was founded by Andre Cronje and launched in 2020.
description.funding: N/A.
description.competition: Centralized asset management platforms such as Betterment and decentralized asset management platforms such as Set.
description.business_model: Yearn is an asset management protocol (variable strategies) built on the Ethereum blockchain.

description.how: Yield Guild Games invests in games and in-game assets / virtual goods (NFTs). YGG also provides scholarships to Axie Infinity players, who then generate yield by playing the game (supply-side revenue).
description.who: YGG tokenholders own and govern the protocol. They currently take a cut of the total earnings generated by the players (protocol revenue). Yield Guild Game's investors include a16z, Fabric, Delphi Digital, etc.
description.what: Yield Guild Games is a play-to-earn gaming guild for blockchain based economies. Yield Guild Games was founded by Gabby Dizon, Beryl Li, Owl of Moistness and launched in 2021.

description.how: Users deposit funds into Yield Yak and earn reward tokens (supply-side revenue).
description.who: YAK token holders own and govern the protocol. They currently take a cut of the rewards earned (protocol revenue).
description.what: Yield Yak is a protocol that auto-compounds yield farming rewards from the Avalanche ecosystem. Yield Yak was founded in 2021 by an anonymous team.

description.how: Miners process transactions and receive fees from users (supply-side revenue).
description.who: ZEC holders own and govern the protocol. They currently do not take a cut of the total transaction fees paid by users (protocol revenue). Zcash’s investors include Fenbushi Capital, Pantera Capital, Digital Currency Group, etc.
description.what: Zcash is a distributed ledger for transfer and store of value (a blockchain). Zcash was founded by Matthew Green, Ian Miers, Christina Garman and launched in 2016.
description.funding: N/A.
description.competition: Proof-of-work blockchains such as Bitcoin, Monero, Litecoin, etc.
description.business_model: Zcash is a proof-of-work (POW) blockchain (fork of Bitcoin).
